# Example YYR4 Daemon Environment Variables
#
# Only necessary if systemd-logind or your user manager does not automatically
# provide a valid graphical session environment for user services.
#
# NOTE: The current XDoTool desktop execution backend ONLY supports X11.
# Wayland is strictly unsupported and will return 'backend unavailable'.
# 
# Instructions:
# 1. Copy this file to ~/.config/yyr4/yyr4d.env
# 2. Adjust DISPLAY and XAUTHORITY to match your actual local user session.
# 3. Ensure permissions are 0600 so other users cannot read it.

XDG_SESSION_TYPE=x11
DISPLAY=:0
# Do NOT use %h here if your systemd version does not expand it in EnvironmentFile.
# Use your absolute path, e.g. /home/example/.Xauthority
XAUTHORITY=/home/example/.Xauthority
